{
  "texts": [
    "Background on Large Language ModelsThe development of Large Language Models has been characterized by rapid advancements and significant investments, when LLMs are trained on extensive datasets to understand and generate human-like text, making them valuable for a wide range of applications from conversational agents to complex problem-solving tools [1], [2].",
    "The Chinese LLM Wai-Lam Cheung is the corresponding author of this study.",
    "Her email: wlcheung nicci hk@outlook.com Kimi, which is developed specifically for understanding and generating Chinese language texts, represents a significant stride in tailoring language technologies to specific linguistic and cultural contexts.",
    "The specialization of LLMs like Kimi highlights the ongoing evolution in the field toward more localized and context-aware models.",
    "Importance of Error Correction in LLMsError correction in LLMs is crucial for several reasons."
  ]
}